  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This program will provide 30 hard of hearing children, aged 0 to 7, using hearing aids or cochlear implants, with the individualized education programs (IEP), including auditory discrimination, oral speaking, pronunciation correction and cognition construction instructed by professional communication trainers and speech/language therapists, according to the levels of hearing impairment and stages of development of these children.</narrative>
